{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-1844","published":"2024-07-12T11:08:31Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:20:13.080931Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-2961"],"summary":"glibc security update","details":"The GNU C Library project provides the core libraries for the GNU system and GNU/Linux systems, as well as many other systems that use Linux as the kernel. These libraries provide critical APIs including ISO C11, POSIX.1-2008, BSD, OS-specific APIs and more. These APIs include such foundational facilities as open, read, write, malloc, printf, getaddrinfo, dlopen, pthread_create, crypt,  login, exit and more.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nThe iconv() function in the GNU C Library versions 2.39 and older may overflow the output buffer passed to it by up to 4 bytes when converting strings to the ISO-2022-CN-EXT character set, which may be used to crash an application or overwrite a neighbouring variable.\n(CVE-2024-2961)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"glibc","ecosystem":"openEuler:22.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/glibc&distro=openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"2.34-150.oe2203sp1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["glibc-nss-devel-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-devel-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","nscd-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","nss_modules-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-locale-source-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-debuginfo-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-common-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-all-langpacks-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-compat-2.17-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-locale-archive-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","libnsl-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-debugsource-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-debugutils-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["glibc-help-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["glibc-2.34-150.oe2203sp1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["glibc-all-langpacks-2.34-150.oe